# NEMETIC STRING
# Fragmented Media Consumption (C002)
# Generated: 2026-03-01 05:13 AM Asia/Shanghai

Φ(FragMedia) = σ(deep|shallow) ∘ ρ(attention|distraction) ∘ λ(focus|drift) ∘ β(consumption|habit) ∘ δγ(overload|fatigue) ∘ μ(boundary|porous) + ε | :scattered

# OPERATOR BREAKDOWN
# σ(deep|shallow)        :: Air  :: Distinction-making between sustained and fragmented processing
# ρ(attention|distraction):: Water :: Relational dynamics between focus capacity and environmental pull
# λ(focus|drift)         :: Fire  :: Directional movement from concentration toward scattered attention
# β(consumption|habit)   :: Wood  :: Feedback loop where media use reinforces attention patterns
# δγ(overload|fatigue)   :: Earth :: Cyclical cost of information saturation leading to cognitive depletion
# μ(boundary|porous)     :: Metal :: Boundary permeability between protected attention and intrusion

# NEMETIC FLOW
⟨Attention|focused⟩ 
  ⊳ ⟨Media|fragmented⟩ 
    → ⟨Cognition|shallow⟩ 
      ⊗ ⟨Knowledge|broad⟩ 
        ⇄ ⟨Understanding|thin⟩

# PARTIAL DERIVATIVES
∂Φ/∂σ = d(distinction)/dt between deep and shallow processing modes
∂Φ/∂ρ = d(relation)/dt between attention capacity and distraction load
∂Φ/∂λ = d(direction)/dt of attention drift toward fragmentation
∂Φ/∂β = d(feedback)/dt between consumption patterns and attention habits
∂Φ/∂δγ = d(cycle)/dt of overload → fatigue → recovery → overload
∂Φ/∂μ = d(boundary)/dt between focused attention and environmental intrusion

